1
00:00:02,550 --> 00:00:04,790
He came out of his castle!

2
00:00:11,060 --> 00:00:14,690
Didn't I tell you? We're screwed!

3
00:00:16,610 --> 00:00:20,570
There you are, you fleas!

4
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:24,720
We're done for!

5
00:01:00,280 --> 00:01:01,600
Germa!

6
00:01:01,600 --> 00:01:02,820
Hurry up!

7
00:01:03,310 --> 00:01:05,850
D-Damn!
Why do I have to...?!

8
00:01:05,850 --> 00:01:08,300
Oh, fine then!

9
00:01:18,490 --> 00:01:20,020
Stop!

10
00:01:24,100 --> 00:01:25,780
Heavenly...

11
00:01:28,880 --> 00:01:30,570
Feuer!

12
00:01:44,750 --> 00:01:45,870
Reiju!

13
00:01:45,870 --> 00:01:48,340
Forget her, Niji! Yonji!

14
00:01:48,340 --> 00:01:52,180
It's her fault for being weak!
Just fulfill the mission!

15
00:01:52,180 --> 00:01:54,660
What a horrid brother I have!

16
00:01:54,660 --> 00:01:57,310
It's okay, though! I can handle myself!

17
00:02:00,820 --> 00:02:05,200
I'm gonna start with you!
Little Germa girl!

18
00:02:07,660 --> 00:02:09,540
Gum-Gum...

19
00:02:10,440 --> 00:02:13,420
Diable Jambe: Crosse...

20
00:02:16,120 --> 00:02:17,800
...Elephant Gun!

21
00:02:18,540 --> 00:02:19,880
...Strike!

22
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:27,240
You told me we weren't going all out!

23
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:30,960
Yeah, I meant you!
It's my job!

24
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:32,480
No fair!

25
00:02:32,480 --> 00:02:33,640
They jumped out.

26
00:02:33,640 --> 00:02:36,560
What are those idiots thinking?!

27
00:04:12,760 --> 00:04:17,640
Why are you guys trying to get away from me?!

28
00:04:22,420 --> 00:04:29,130
Do you remember what you said to me, Straw Hat?
When you were on Fishman Island?!

29
00:04:30,080 --> 00:04:33,920
You said you'd kick my ass.

30
00:04:37,650 --> 00:04:39,960
Monkey D. Luffy...

31
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:42,970
I'll remember that name.

32
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:46,970
Come! To the New World!

33
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:51,260
Sure. Just you wait!

34
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:56,170
I'll kick your ass in the New World...

35
00:04:56,900 --> 00:05:00,570
and make Fishman Island my territory!

36
00:05:00,570 --> 00:05:04,830
Remember what you said to me
on this island?

37
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:10,080
You said that you'd be the ones
who will come out on top.

38
00:05:10,080 --> 00:05:13,800
You're the one who
hasn't become the king of the pirates.

39
00:05:13,800 --> 00:05:15,840
That's all.

40
00:05:16,340 --> 00:05:18,840
I'm here to pick another fight with you!

41
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:22,680
Don't be cocky just because
you're an emperor!

42
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:25,190
I'm going to take Sanji back!

43
00:05:25,190 --> 00:05:29,020
And in the end, we're the ones who'll win!

44
00:05:29,020 --> 00:05:33,950
And now you're trying to run?
You coward!

45
00:05:33,950 --> 00:05:35,680
C... C...

46
00:05:35,680 --> 00:05:38,060
Co... ward...?

47
00:05:39,230 --> 00:05:42,020
Don't listen to her, Luffy!
She's provoking you!

48
00:05:42,020 --> 00:05:43,710
Just one punch!

49
00:05:43,710 --> 00:05:44,900
Hey! Luffy!

50
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,610
Yeah, I said those things!

51
00:05:47,610 --> 00:05:49,820
Big Mom!

52
00:06:12,040 --> 00:06:15,920
In the end,
the one who will be king of the pirates...

53
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:24,530
is me !

54
00:06:52,850 --> 00:06:54,690
Good job, Germa!

55
00:06:54,690 --> 00:06:57,040
Keep protecting me just like that!

56
00:06:57,040 --> 00:06:58,720
You fools!

57
00:06:59,220 --> 00:07:01,730
Anybody who rebels against Mama...

58
00:07:01,730 --> 00:07:04,920
will be burned to death by me!

59
00:07:05,720 --> 00:07:07,570
This one's bad news!

60
00:07:07,570 --> 00:07:09,600
That damn Oven, then?

61
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,740
I'll take care of you two first!

62
00:07:20,040 --> 00:07:22,540
I'll leave the rest to you!

63
00:07:22,540 --> 00:07:24,740
Burn to death?

64
00:07:24,740 --> 00:07:28,450
I'll beat you up before you get a chance!

65
00:07:28,450 --> 00:07:30,470
How arrogant!

66
00:07:30,470 --> 00:07:33,160
In any case, just get me over the wall!

67
00:07:33,160 --> 00:07:35,540
That's all I'm trying to do!

68
00:07:36,100 --> 00:07:38,250
There are still more of them!

69
00:07:43,390 --> 00:07:46,630
If we clear that wall, we can escape!

70
00:07:46,630 --> 00:07:48,440
Lick.

71
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:51,350
I'm not gonna let them get away.

72
00:07:51,700 --> 00:07:53,540
Candy Wall!

73
00:07:57,230 --> 00:07:58,440
Oh, no!

74
00:08:01,920 --> 00:08:03,570
What?!

75
00:08:03,570 --> 00:08:07,440
W-What the hell is that?!

76
00:08:08,300 --> 00:08:10,460
Perospero must've done it...

77
00:08:10,460 --> 00:08:13,240
That was our last hope...

78
00:08:17,100 --> 00:08:21,080
It's over... Oh, my freedom...

79
00:08:21,080 --> 00:08:23,870
Crap! It'll swallow us!
Turn around!

80
00:08:23,870 --> 00:08:26,550
No, keep moving forward!

81
00:08:35,560 --> 00:08:36,600
Black...

82
00:08:37,420 --> 00:08:37,980
Bug!

83
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:47,530
Go!

84
00:08:47,530 --> 00:08:49,320
What?! But...

85
00:08:58,250 --> 00:08:59,760
Oops...

86
00:09:01,540 --> 00:09:06,430
You saved us! Germa 66!

87
00:09:06,430 --> 00:09:10,670
Yay! He got through the wall of candy!
Only Germa could've done it!

88
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:14,650
Go! Caesar!

89
00:09:14,650 --> 00:09:17,000
He's a loser though!

90
00:09:17,670 --> 00:09:22,490
Dammit! I got this far now!
I don't wanna die!

91
00:09:22,490 --> 00:09:27,910
Once I get over the wall, I...
I can be...

92
00:09:27,910 --> 00:09:31,080
free!

93
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:39,590
Th-The secret undersea treasure,
the Tamate Box, is right there...

94
00:09:41,510 --> 00:09:45,080
I can't believe it got stuck right there...

95
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:48,280
I have no choice. I gotta jump off...

96
00:09:48,280 --> 00:09:51,590
What are you going to do
with the Tamate Box, Du Feld?

97
00:09:51,590 --> 00:09:53,620
Y-You're...

98
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:57,450
Stussy! Have you been watching me?

99
00:10:04,290 --> 00:10:06,310
Ow, ow, ow...

100
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:09,400
But now I can see what's in it...

101
00:10:11,680 --> 00:10:16,970
The secret undersea treasure...
Let's see what's inside!

102
00:10:25,180 --> 00:10:26,440
Flying Finger Pistol...

103
00:10:26,440 --> 00:10:30,200
The Tamate Box belongs to the World Government now,

104
00:10:33,760 --> 00:10:35,620
fool.

105
00:10:35,620 --> 00:10:39,120
Of course, you'll still take the blame for it.

106
00:10:39,660 --> 00:10:42,120
Can you write that story for me,

107
00:10:42,120 --> 00:10:44,580
Morgans?

108
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,580
She knew I was here!

109
00:10:44,580 --> 00:10:48,610
Sure, but can I at least
get the scoop on its contents?

110
00:10:48,610 --> 00:10:52,610
Yes, go ahead.
You sure do know how to play the game.

111
00:10:52,610 --> 00:10:54,470
It's no wonder you're such a good spin doctor.

112
00:10:54,470 --> 00:10:56,760
I'm a newsman! I'll sue you!

113
00:11:00,230 --> 00:11:02,020
– What?!
– No!

114
00:11:09,850 --> 00:11:12,190
Once I take care of Kaido...

115
00:11:14,770 --> 00:11:16,650
I'm coming back for you!

116
00:11:17,520 --> 00:11:20,570
Big Mom!

117
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:29,330
This is nothing!

118
00:11:32,460 --> 00:11:33,630
Luffy...

119
00:11:35,170 --> 00:11:38,380
You said you'd punch her once!

120
00:11:38,380 --> 00:11:40,900
Kaido?

121
00:11:43,760 --> 00:11:48,520
You'll never beat that thing...

122
00:11:50,070 --> 00:11:54,520
And more importantly,

123
00:11:55,020 --> 00:12:01,570
you must be dreaming if you think
you're getting out of my territory alive!

124
00:12:07,450 --> 00:12:09,240
Big Mom!

125
00:12:10,390 --> 00:12:14,040
Our dream has already ended...

126
00:12:15,250 --> 00:12:19,390
In the wake of a dream of just 66 days,

127
00:12:19,390 --> 00:12:23,920
our ancestors were left as wandering ghosts,
unable to set foot on their homeland!

128
00:12:25,390 --> 00:12:28,510
And now I have disgraced their memory!

129
00:12:34,440 --> 00:12:36,520
Judge!

130
00:12:40,480 --> 00:12:42,340
I can't believe I entrusted

131
00:12:42,340 --> 00:12:47,150
a person like you with the soul
of three centuries of longing...

132
00:12:47,150 --> 00:12:49,950
I despise myself for it!

133
00:12:54,470 --> 00:12:57,190
That's not going to work!

134
00:12:59,000 --> 00:13:01,640
No need to worry. You're going to die,

135
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:05,260
and then I shall use your advanced technology...

136
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:11,640
and bring peace to the world!

137
00:13:26,060 --> 00:13:27,560
Thunderbolt!

138
00:13:32,190 --> 00:13:33,230
Father!

139
00:13:41,490 --> 00:13:42,780
Did he die?!

140
00:13:42,780 --> 00:13:43,690
Father!

141
00:13:43,690 --> 00:13:45,570
Hey, wait, guards!

142
00:13:45,570 --> 00:13:49,040
Are you guys abandoning us–

143
00:14:00,110 --> 00:14:02,720
Katakuri!

144
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:04,680
You were so close.

145
00:14:05,220 --> 00:14:07,220
You just had a bit more to go.

146
00:14:14,680 --> 00:14:16,100
Sparking...

147
00:14:16,780 --> 00:14:17,780
Figure!

148
00:14:20,400 --> 00:14:24,400
Don't worry. We'll do our part! Just go!

149
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,990
You don't have to tell me!

150
00:14:27,870 --> 00:14:31,160
You think you caught me cold?

151
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:36,620
I don't think you value your life.

152
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:39,210
Threatening me is useless.

153
00:14:39,210 --> 00:14:43,130
Unfortunately... I don't get scared.

154
00:14:47,030 --> 00:14:49,860
Don't let them get away!
Shoot, shoot!

155
00:14:49,860 --> 00:14:51,700
Go! You can make it-rero !

156
00:14:51,700 --> 00:14:53,540
That's it! Go!

157
00:14:53,540 --> 00:14:55,540
You can do it, Caesar!

158
00:14:55,540 --> 00:14:57,040
You're still a loser, though!

159
00:14:57,040 --> 00:14:58,900
Huh? What did you just–

160
00:15:01,840 --> 00:15:04,270
Watch out, you...

161
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,050
What?

162
00:15:09,020 --> 00:15:10,950
– Hey! Get out of my way!
– Hey! Get out of my way!

163
00:15:10,950 --> 00:15:13,310
– Huh? Who are you?!
– Huh? Who are you?!

164
00:15:15,860 --> 00:15:17,270
– Are you me?!
– Are you me?!

165
00:15:17,270 --> 00:15:20,210
– No, you can't be me!
– No, you can't be me!

166
00:15:20,210 --> 00:15:24,660
It's me, Caesar Clown!

167
00:15:24,660 --> 00:15:25,950
Brûlée?!

168
00:15:28,330 --> 00:15:30,380
I won't let you escape!

169
00:15:30,380 --> 00:15:34,390
You people did a lot of bad things to me,

170
00:15:34,390 --> 00:15:38,380
and now I can finally settle the score!

171
00:15:42,640 --> 00:15:45,760
This isn't good, Caesar!

172
00:15:57,110 --> 00:15:59,450
They all got taken out?

173
00:16:02,790 --> 00:16:04,620
Oh, no...

174
00:16:16,090 --> 00:16:18,130
This is the end...

175
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,220
No...

176
00:16:22,220 --> 00:16:24,600
Germa!

177
00:16:25,350 --> 00:16:29,440
If we don't do something,
everyone will die.

178
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:31,020
I don't want that!

179
00:16:31,020 --> 00:16:32,700
Then...

180
00:16:37,070 --> 00:16:40,410
there's only one option.

181
00:16:43,990 --> 00:16:46,700
Instead of sitting back and waiting for our deaths...

182
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:50,040
...we'll fight, right?

183
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:52,290
– I'm going too!
– Me too!

184
00:16:52,290 --> 00:16:54,630
We're going too, of course!

185
00:16:54,630 --> 00:16:56,880
I have no choice...

186
00:17:12,190 --> 00:17:14,390
The Tamate Box!

187
00:17:26,390 --> 00:17:30,560
All right, let's begin...

188
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:33,420
the executions.

189
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:55,040
What's going on?

190
00:18:20,480 --> 00:18:24,110
A short time ago...

191
00:18:29,700 --> 00:18:34,450
Luffy and the others saved the Ryugu Kingdom
from the New Fishman Pirates

192
00:18:34,450 --> 00:18:39,140
and were given the Tamate Box by King Neptune as a reward.

193
00:18:39,140 --> 00:18:40,500
But...

194
00:18:40,500 --> 00:18:42,180
Your Majesty!

195
00:18:42,180 --> 00:18:48,360
Regarding all of the treasure you're giving
to Luffy-kun and the others if they can find it...

196
00:18:48,360 --> 00:18:52,430
do you suppose we could
ask for just the Tamate Box back?

197
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:54,250
What are you suggesting?

198
00:18:54,250 --> 00:18:58,520
I'd never ask someone to return a gift I gave them!

199
00:18:58,520 --> 00:19:02,270
Well, what if there isn't treasure inside...

200
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:04,400
but a bomb, instead?

201
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,650
What?

202
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:08,320
It'll explode if they open it?!

203
00:19:08,320 --> 00:19:10,870
I must ask them to return it immediately.

204
00:19:13,330 --> 00:19:17,830
You gave all of the treasure... to Big Mom?!

205
00:19:17,830 --> 00:19:21,000
Maybe it won't explode,
minister of the right.

206
00:19:21,000 --> 00:19:25,120
Your Majesty, it's good to think positive.

207
00:19:27,380 --> 00:19:30,010
Now, back to the present.

208
00:19:33,490 --> 00:19:35,540
From the ceiling of the east second floor midbaum,

209
00:19:35,540 --> 00:19:38,730
a giant crack is running through
the red-bean midbaum meeting room!

210
00:19:38,730 --> 00:19:42,610
Not just a crack! It's a complete split!

211
00:19:42,610 --> 00:19:46,110
This is the red-bean third floor midbaum third floor!
What's happening?!

212
00:19:46,110 --> 00:19:49,030
The room is starting to tilt!

213
00:19:49,030 --> 00:19:51,410
It's not an earthquake!

214
00:19:51,530 --> 00:19:54,950
I heard an enormous explosion earlier!

215
00:19:54,950 --> 00:19:57,950
– Are we under attack?!
– It won't stop tilting!

216
00:19:57,950 --> 00:19:59,710
What's going on?

217
00:20:00,420 --> 00:20:02,790
N-No way...

218
00:20:03,380 --> 00:20:06,170
It's falling over-bon...

219
00:20:06,970 --> 00:20:09,550
Whole Cake Chateau!

220
00:20:10,590 --> 00:20:14,100
It's falling over-bon!

221
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:16,600
Cock-a-doodle-do!

222
00:20:24,820 --> 00:20:26,610
Did an enemy shoot a cannon?

223
00:20:26,610 --> 00:20:31,190
We're in the stronghold of an emperor!
How could someone invade this place?!

224
00:20:31,190 --> 00:20:33,540
Then it really was an explosion!

225
00:20:36,330 --> 00:20:38,830
What in the world just exploded?!

226
00:20:38,830 --> 00:20:40,580
Please, make it stop!

227
00:20:40,580 --> 00:20:42,550
We're all going to die!

228
00:20:42,550 --> 00:20:45,970
Does it have something to do with
the rooftop wedding?!

229
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:04,820
This has to be a joke!

230
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:08,940
But this is big news!

231
00:21:13,450 --> 00:21:15,920
Was that... what I think it was?

232
00:21:15,920 --> 00:21:17,170
It must be!

233
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:22,460
The timing was dead-on!
What else could have exploded like that?

234
00:21:23,110 --> 00:21:26,840
But... why the Tamate Box?!

235
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:31,680
Everyone, hold onto something!

236
00:21:34,140 --> 00:21:36,060
Where did Straw Hat and the others go?

237
00:21:37,060 --> 00:21:39,140
What just happened?!

238
00:21:39,140 --> 00:21:40,860
I don't know...

239
00:21:40,860 --> 00:21:45,330
In any case, it bought us some time!
They were just about to kill all of us!

240
00:21:51,160 --> 00:21:55,210
What's going on?! What's happening here?!

241
00:22:07,110 --> 00:22:09,790
Something just saved us...

242
00:22:09,790 --> 00:22:12,440
I think it's a bit too early...

243
00:22:13,820 --> 00:22:15,860
to say that for sure!

244
00:22:16,450 --> 00:22:18,910
It's an emergency, Mama!

245
00:22:18,910 --> 00:22:25,120
A sudden explosion is causing
Whole Cake Chateau to collapse!

246
00:22:38,300 --> 00:22:40,220
Something's going on outside!

247
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:43,590
We can't feel anything from inside Bege's body...

248
00:22:43,590 --> 00:22:45,640
What is going on?

249
00:22:47,310 --> 00:22:50,640
I'm not sure. But...

250
00:22:50,640 --> 00:22:53,520
there's a massive panic outside.

251
00:22:54,820 --> 00:22:56,580
Could it be...

252
00:22:56,580 --> 00:23:00,610
that Whole Cake Chateau itself is shaking?

253
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:03,320
What kind of joke is this?!

254
00:23:03,320 --> 00:23:06,120
Am I dreaming right now?!

255
00:23:08,450 --> 00:23:10,080
Look, Caesar!

256
00:23:11,840 --> 00:23:14,420
It's a big mess....

257
00:23:17,300 --> 00:23:19,610
How did this happen?!

258
00:23:20,350 --> 00:23:23,680
Who did it and what did they do?!

259
00:23:23,680 --> 00:23:25,210
Brothers...

260
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:27,380
Sisters...

261
00:23:28,100 --> 00:23:30,480
Oh, my family!

262
00:23:33,030 --> 00:23:35,190
I can't stop!

263
00:23:35,190 --> 00:23:36,310
Mama!

264
00:23:48,820 --> 00:23:52,530
Mama!

265
00:24:07,460 --> 00:24:10,140
Terrific!

266
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:14,060
I don't know who did it,
but I gotta thank them!

267
00:24:14,060 --> 00:24:17,190
We didn't even have to assassinate her!

268
00:24:17,190 --> 00:24:19,390
Now,

269
00:24:19,390 --> 00:24:22,740
Emperor Big Mom's pirate crew has been...

270
00:24:22,740 --> 00:24:25,310
annihilated!

271
00:24:33,380 --> 00:24:34,760
There's no escape!

272
00:24:43,470 --> 00:24:47,440
The castle's bigger than the city... We can't escape!

273
00:24:47,440 --> 00:24:50,650
No one's fast enough... to run away in time!

274
00:25:01,280 --> 00:25:02,410
Big Brother!

275
00:25:05,370 --> 00:25:06,750
Calm down.

276
00:25:10,080 --> 00:25:14,590
Big news! This is big news!

277
00:25:14,590 --> 00:25:16,840
Aren't you worried for your own life?

278
00:25:16,840 --> 00:25:19,180
Oh, right! I can't fly!

279
00:25:24,520 --> 00:25:25,560
But...

280
00:25:26,270 --> 00:25:31,810
if this is the end of the Big Mom Pirates,

281
00:25:32,520 --> 00:25:34,610
it definitely is big news.

282
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,120
Hey!

283
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:47,330
Sanji-kun !

284
00:25:48,740 --> 00:25:49,730
This way!

285
00:25:49,730 --> 00:25:51,440
Please hurry up!

286
00:25:51,440 --> 00:25:53,240
Sanji! Luffy!

287
00:25:54,830 --> 00:25:57,080
You're alive!

288
00:25:59,160 --> 00:26:01,700
– Sorry I kept you waiting!
– You're too reckless!

289
00:26:01,700 --> 00:26:03,500
Honestly!

290
00:26:03,500 --> 00:26:05,720
I'm so relieved.

291
00:26:06,090 --> 00:26:08,900
Go, Caesar! As far as you can fly!

292
00:26:08,900 --> 00:26:11,090
You don't have to tell me that!

293
00:26:11,090 --> 00:26:13,470
Run away! Run away! Run away!

294
00:26:15,660 --> 00:26:16,930
They're gone.

295
00:26:18,060 --> 00:26:19,640
Mission complete!

296
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:20,940
Withdraw!

297
00:26:20,940 --> 00:26:22,450
Roger.

298
00:26:34,580 --> 00:26:37,000
♪ Soft and fluffy... ♪

299
00:26:37,000 --> 00:26:40,330
♪ Moist and fluffy... ♪

300
00:26:40,330 --> 00:26:44,840
♪ In life, there's no such thing ♪

301
00:26:52,930 --> 00:26:55,550
Hey, are you okay?

302
00:26:58,980 --> 00:27:00,850
Oh, no...

303
00:27:00,850 --> 00:27:02,980
This is it!

304
00:27:03,270 --> 00:27:06,440
♪ Veränderung... ♪

305
00:27:03,270 --> 00:27:06,440
Transformation

306
00:27:07,380 --> 00:27:08,440
♪ Gourmet! ♪

307
00:27:34,340 --> 00:27:36,100
What the?!

308
00:27:52,150 --> 00:27:53,530
Mama!

309
00:27:54,260 --> 00:27:55,780
Mama!

310
00:27:59,780 --> 00:28:01,540
That was close.

311
00:28:11,500 --> 00:28:13,310
Heavy cream?

312
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:15,760
We're gonna get swept away!

313
00:28:20,260 --> 00:28:22,810
– Is this...
– Sponge cake?

314
00:28:37,250 --> 00:28:39,210
What happened?

315
00:28:41,540 --> 00:28:46,170
Whole Cake Chateau turned into
an actual whole cake...

316
00:28:46,170 --> 00:28:50,730
That saved us...
The head chef must've done it.

317
00:28:50,730 --> 00:28:53,260
I thought I was gonna die!

318
00:28:57,390 --> 00:28:59,680
Are you okay, Mama?

319
00:28:59,680 --> 00:29:01,410
Cake...

320
00:29:01,410 --> 00:29:04,980
My castle turned into a cake...

321
00:29:07,190 --> 00:29:11,750
Sweets created by Streusen's ability

322
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:15,200
will keep you from getting hungry,
but they taste bad.

323
00:29:15,200 --> 00:29:15,950
Mama!

324
00:29:18,870 --> 00:29:20,710
I'm glad you're okay.

325
00:29:21,960 --> 00:29:27,720
Dammit... My wedding cake...

326
00:29:28,470 --> 00:29:31,680
Cake...

327
00:29:33,890 --> 00:29:35,340
Are you okay?

328
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:36,810
I need your help!

329
00:29:36,810 --> 00:29:39,560
All right! You're okay now.

330
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:41,440
I thought I was gonna die.

331
00:29:41,440 --> 00:29:44,410
I'm gonna be crushed by the cake!

332
00:29:44,410 --> 00:29:46,520
I hear a voice over there!

333
00:29:46,520 --> 00:29:48,690
Hurry and help that person!

334
00:29:50,350 --> 00:29:51,900
Th-That's...

335
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:55,370
Minister Mont d'Or! What happened?!

336
00:29:55,370 --> 00:29:58,670
We thought the city would be crushed!

337
00:29:58,670 --> 00:30:01,020
– Shut up!
– What?!

338
00:30:01,020 --> 00:30:03,360
It's not over yet!

339
00:30:03,360 --> 00:30:07,490
The ones who tried to assassinate Mama got away!

340
00:30:07,490 --> 00:30:10,820
They must still be nearby!

341
00:30:10,820 --> 00:30:14,780
Contact every tarte base in Totto Land!

342
00:30:14,780 --> 00:30:19,120
Don't let a single one of

343
00:30:19,120 --> 00:30:22,200
the Straw Hat Pirates or Fire Tank Pirates escape!

344
00:30:29,150 --> 00:30:31,420
I guess this is far enough.

345
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:32,460
Get out!

346
00:30:40,720 --> 00:30:44,460
Thank you, Bege!
We thought we were goners...

347
00:30:44,460 --> 00:30:46,160
I don't need your thanks!

348
00:30:46,160 --> 00:30:49,810
It makes me sick when I feel
like I've done something good.

349
00:30:49,810 --> 00:30:53,530
I'm the one who carried you! You jerks!

350
00:30:53,530 --> 00:30:55,110
Shut up, loser!

351
00:30:55,110 --> 00:30:59,700
Do you remember what you did
to those kids on Punk Hazard?

352
00:30:59,700 --> 00:31:03,200
We don't need you anymore, so...
go drop dead.

353
00:31:04,530 --> 00:31:08,590
Hey! How dare you speak to a genius like that!

354
00:31:08,590 --> 00:31:13,080
I could turn this place into
a poison gas trap if I wanted to!

355
00:31:14,960 --> 00:31:17,760
Here. Take your heart.

356
00:31:22,510 --> 00:31:24,680
It's my... my... my...

357
00:31:30,810 --> 00:31:32,790
You're free, too.

358
00:31:32,790 --> 00:31:34,530
You should've crushed it.

359
00:31:35,440 --> 00:31:36,780
No!

360
00:31:37,360 --> 00:31:39,570
Oh, please!

361
00:31:41,820 --> 00:31:43,240
You should've crushed it.

362
00:31:52,180 --> 00:31:55,180
My heart...

363
00:31:55,180 --> 00:31:59,430
My heart is back!

364
00:31:59,850 --> 00:32:02,180
We'll never cross paths again!

365
00:32:02,180 --> 00:32:06,270
Goodbye, idiots and you stupid girl!

366
00:32:06,270 --> 00:32:07,540
Why did it collapse?

367
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:10,780
Hey! Hey!

368
00:32:07,540 --> 00:32:09,840
Yeah, it was sudden.

369
00:32:09,840 --> 00:32:11,970
What happened?

370
00:32:10,770 --> 00:32:12,540
Bye!

371
00:32:12,520 --> 00:32:13,430
Hey!

372
00:32:11,970 --> 00:32:13,430
I have no idea.

373
00:32:13,430 --> 00:32:15,820
Hey, guys!

374
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:17,150
Father!

375
00:32:17,730 --> 00:32:21,160
As far as I can tell, it looks like Big Mom...

376
00:32:21,160 --> 00:32:23,910
and her family have all survived-rero !

377
00:32:24,570 --> 00:32:28,440
The fallen castle turned into an actual cake!

378
00:32:28,440 --> 00:32:32,000
Streusen must've done it.

379
00:32:33,080 --> 00:32:37,370
He's always been a mystery to me.

380
00:32:39,920 --> 00:32:43,680
I'm sure he's more than just the head chef.

381
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:46,850
He's probably pretty tough in a fight.

382
00:32:48,720 --> 00:32:52,440
So, the Big Mom Pirates aren't totally wiped out...

383
00:32:52,440 --> 00:32:54,870
they've got good luck.

384
00:32:55,650 --> 00:32:58,610
But it's fine. The chateau collapsed.

385
00:32:58,610 --> 00:33:00,570
I can feel good about that.

386
00:33:00,570 --> 00:33:03,410
Goodbye, Straw Hat!

387
00:33:03,410 --> 00:33:05,690
So, all that's left is to get away!

388
00:33:05,690 --> 00:33:10,190
That's always been the plan...
We just hit the biggest obstacles right at the start!

389
00:33:10,190 --> 00:33:12,750
All right. Let's run, then.

390
00:33:12,750 --> 00:33:15,740
This is where we part ways, Straw Hat.

391
00:33:15,740 --> 00:33:17,590
What? Is that so?

392
00:33:17,590 --> 00:33:20,420
We weren't able to assassinate Big Mom,

393
00:33:20,420 --> 00:33:23,910
so there's no reason for us to keep working together.

394
00:33:23,910 --> 00:33:28,100
You're right about that.
And you guys had best hurry, too.

395
00:33:28,100 --> 00:33:33,170
Even by ship, it'll take you a full day to get out of Big Mom's territory.

396
00:33:33,170 --> 00:33:34,520
That's true!

397
00:33:34,520 --> 00:33:36,560
Good luck!

398
00:33:38,770 --> 00:33:40,110
Castle Tank!

399
00:33:47,870 --> 00:33:50,580
"The Straw Hats went that way. ->"

400
00:33:47,870 --> 00:33:50,580
"The Straw Hats went that way"?

401
00:33:50,580 --> 00:33:52,960
Is this sign really necessary?!

402
00:33:52,960 --> 00:33:55,460
Shut up! It's every man for himself now!

403
00:33:55,460 --> 00:33:59,240
Father!
At least let us say goodbye-rero !

404
00:33:59,240 --> 00:34:02,050
Yeah, Nami's my friend now!

405
00:34:02,050 --> 00:34:06,220
We ain't here to make friends!
It's time to begin the real escape!

406
00:34:07,300 --> 00:34:11,050
Okay, we'll go pick up the Shark Submerge

407
00:34:11,050 --> 00:34:14,090
and bring it right back to the Sunny !

408
00:34:14,090 --> 00:34:16,550
Yeah. Be careful!

409
00:34:16,550 --> 00:34:20,100
We're going to hurry back
to the coastline where we landed!

410
00:34:20,870 --> 00:34:24,110
Assemble two squads, Daifuku.

411
00:34:24,110 --> 00:34:25,450
Okay.

412
00:34:25,950 --> 00:34:29,750
We'll split up into two groups
and pursue them!

413
00:34:29,750 --> 00:34:35,550
One group, bring back Straw Hat's head!
And the other, bring back Bege's!

414
00:34:41,350 --> 00:34:42,760
Mama.

415
00:34:45,390 --> 00:34:49,210
Don't worry.
We won't let any of them escape...

416
00:34:49,210 --> 00:34:51,270
Cake...

417
00:34:53,190 --> 00:34:57,030
Its ingredients were carefully selected...

418
00:34:57,030 --> 00:35:00,940
It was going to be the
best wedding cake ever...

419
00:35:00,940 --> 00:35:05,990
I was looking forward to it...

420
00:35:11,960 --> 00:35:16,590
Wedding cake...

421
00:35:17,900 --> 00:35:19,270
Mama?

422
00:35:23,930 --> 00:35:29,730
Where's my wedding cake?!

423
00:35:30,560 --> 00:35:32,480
Not now...

424
00:35:32,480 --> 00:35:35,270
Bring it to me now!

